/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 48w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/64x43/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 64w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/96x64/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 96w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/128x85/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 128w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/256x171/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 256w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/376x251/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 376w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/384x256/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 384w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/415x277/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 415w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/480x320/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 480w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/540x360/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 540w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/640x427/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 640w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/750x500/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 750w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/828x552/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 828w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/1080x720/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 1080w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/1200x800/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 1200w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/1440x960/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 1440w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/1920x1280/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 1920w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/2048x1365/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 2048w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/2400x1600/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg 2400w" src="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1790x846/2400x1600/filters:focal(895x423:896x424):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429532/TAO.jpg" decoding="async" data-nimg="responsive" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/></span><div class="duet--media--caption pt-6 font-polysans-mono text-12 font-light leading-130 tracking-1"> <cite class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup inline not-italic text-gray-63 dark:text-gray-bd [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-63 [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-bd dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-gray [&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-63 dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:text-gray-bd dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray">Image: University of Tokyo</cite></div></figure></div></div></div></div><div class="relative md:mx-auto md:flex md:max-w-container-md lg:max-w-none"><div class="duet--article--article-body-component-container clearfix sm:ml-auto md:ml-100 md:max-w-article-body lg:mx-100"><div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">The University of Tokyo Atacama Observatory (TAO) <a href="https://www.ioa.s.u-tokyo.ac.jp/TAO/en/news/20240430/index.html">officially opened</a> on Tuesday after 26 years of planning and construction. Sitting 18,500 feet high on Mount Chajnantor in the Atacama Desert in Chile, the 6.5-meter optical-infrared TAO telescope is now the highest in the world. </p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">TAO replaces a smaller version of itself called MiniTAO, which held the highest telescope distinction before it. It beats the <a href="https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2022EGUGA..2410801A/abstract">Chacaltaya Observatory</a>, owned by the University of Madrid and sitting 17,191 feet on Mount Chacaltaya in Bolivia. </p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">The next three record holders in the top five are also in Chile’s Atacama desert: <a href="https://cosmology.ucsd.edu/Polarbear/site/">the James Ax Observatory</a> (17,100 feet); the <a href="https://www.nist.gov/measuring-cosmos/atacama-cosmology-telescope">Atacama Cosmology Telescope</a> (17,030 feet); and the Llano de Chajnantor Observatory (<a href="https://www.mpifr-bonn.mpg.de/769800/general">sources</a> <a href="https://sites.astro.caltech.edu/chajnantor/site/">vary</a>; about 16,700 feet). Many of the world’s major observatories are built in the high-altitude, northeastern area of Chile, near Bolivia, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/04/18/science/astronomy-telescopes-magellan-chile.html">because of its clear skies</a>. The country’s <a href="https://astrobites.org/2019/09/10/astronomical-observatories-and-indigenous-communities-in-chile/">tax exemptions for such projects</a> help, too.</p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">Being so high up means far less moisture in the air; TAO can observe “almost the entire range of near-infrared wavelengths,” including mid-infrared. No other earthbound telescope can do that, <a href="https://phys.org/news/2024-04-observatory-chile-highest-world-aims.html">Phys.org notes</a>. The University of Tokyo writes that such terrestrial observatories are capable of taking higher-resolution shots of space, thanks to their larger apertures, than their space-based counterparts. The telescope will be used to learn about “the birth of galaxies and the origin of planets” starting in 2025, according to the University of Tokyo’s announcement.</p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component clear-both block"><div class="my-9"><div class="transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out"><div class="fixed inset-0 h-[110vh] w-full bg-white transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out z-[-1] cursor-default opacity-0" role="button" aria-label="Close" tabindex="0"></div><div role="button" aria-label="Zoom" tabindex="0" class="visible z-30 w-full origin-center transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out cursor-zoom-in"><figure class="transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out lg:mx-0"><div><div class="duet--media--content-warning relative" style="padding-top:133.33333333333331%"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0"><img alt="A diagram of the telescope, labeled." src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="A diagram of the telescope, labeled." loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover" sizes="(max-width: 1023px) 100vw, 744px" srcSet="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:540x720/376x501/filters:focal(270x360:271x361):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25429527/Diagram_TAO_telescope.jpg 376w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:540x720/384x512/filte